Share an announcement during a Q&A session in Slido
As a Webex Meetings or Webex Webinars host, share information with participants during a Q&A session by sending an announcement. The message appears at the top of the Q&A panel for all participants to see.
Slido is available in Webex Meetings. You can use Slido in plans for up to 10,000 users in Webex Webinars on version 41.9 and later sites. Slido polls are available for up to 10,000 attendees, while quizzes are available for up to 5,000 users.
You can choose whether you want to show the announcement immediately or save it for later.
Before you begin
Make sure you've turned on the Q&A feature in Slido.
1
During a meeting or webinar, go to the Q&A tab in Slido, and then click Review.
2
Click Create announcement , and then type your announcement.
3
Click Announce now to send the announcement immediately.
Click Save to activate it later.
4
When you want to stop showing the announcement, click Stop announcement.